<Link id="l01268" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1268"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The main task here is merging identical sets.  This is usually a waste</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01269" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1269"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; of time (although the hash code minimizes the overhead), but can win</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01270" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1270"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; big if REG&#95;ICASE is being used.  REG&#95;ICASE, by the way, is why the hash</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01271" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1271"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; is done using addition rather than xor -- all ASCII &#91;aA&#93; sets xor to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01272" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1272"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; the same value!</Highlight></CodeLine>
